heading('7. Source Code with Comments',1)
heading('7.1 Commenting Approach',2); p('The reviewed source already includes focused comments around non-obvious behaviour, notably price conversion, category-event communication, modal lifecycle handling, gallery asset reuse and contact-form limitations. The code is not over-commented. The snippets below explain the important logic without rewriting the full source.')
heading('7.2 Shared Cart State - App.jsx',2); code('''const handleAddToCart = (product) => {\n  const normalizedProduct = { ...product,\n    name: product?.name || product?.title || "Product",\n    price: toNumber(product?.price ?? product?.cost ?? product?.amount ?? 0),\n  };\n  setCartItems((prev) => {\n    const existing = prev.find((item) => item.id === normalizedProduct.id);\n    if (existing) return prev.map((item) =>\n      item.id === normalizedProduct.id\n        ? { ...item, quantity: item.quantity + 1 } : item);\n    return [...prev, { ...normalizedProduct, quantity: 1 }];\n  });\n  setIsCartOpen(true);\n};'''); p('This function normalizes flexible product-like inputs, increments an existing cart line or appends a new one, then opens the drawer. It is held in App so Navbar, ProductSection and CartDrawer can share the same state.')
heading('7.3 Derived Filtering - ProductSection.jsx',2); code('''let result = allProducts.filter((product) => {\n  if (filters.category && product.category !== filters.category) return false;\n  if (filters.type && product.type !== filters.type) return false;\n  if (filters.color && product.color !== filters.color) return false;\n  if (filters.brand && product.brand !== filters.brand) return false;\n  if (filters.price && toNumber(product.price) > Number(filters.price)) return false;\n  return true;\n});\n// result is then copied and sorted by rating, id or numeric price.'''); p('The predicate only applies a criterion when its filter value is present. toNumber removes commas from stored price strings before numeric comparison.')
heading('7.4 Modal Lifecycle - ProductModal.jsx',2); code('''useEffect(() => {\n  const handleKeyDown = (e) => { if (e.key === "Escape") onClose(); };\n  document.addEventListener("keydown", handleKeyDown);\n  document.body.style.overflow = "hidden";\n  return () => {\n    document.removeEventListener("keydown", handleKeyDown);\n    document.body.style.overflow = "";\n  };\n}, [onClose]);'''); p('When mounted, the modal listens for Escape and disables page scrolling. Its cleanup restores both; backdrop clicks call onClose while clicks within the modal stop propagation.')
heading('7.5 Contact Validation - Contact.jsx',2); code('''const validate = (values) => {\n  const nextErrors = {};\n  if (!values.name.trim()) nextErrors.name = "Please enter your name.";\n  if (!values.email.trim()) nextErrors.email = "Please enter your email.";\n  else if (!/^\\S+@\\S+\\.\\S+$/.test(values.email))\n    nextErrors.email = "Please enter a valid email address.";\n  if (!values.message.trim()) nextErrors.message = "Please enter a message.";\n  return nextErrors;\n};'''); p('The validation runs entirely in the browser. A valid submission clears the fields and displays a confirmation but does not send or store a message.')

heading('8. User Guide',1)
heading('8.1 Introduction and System Requirements',2); p('Fanimation is used through a modern web browser with JavaScript enabled. No user account is required for the current demonstrator. Internet access is only needed when the app is deployed or served remotely; the submitted source can run locally with Node.js and npm.')
heading('8.2 Starting the Application',2); p('A non-technical user normally opens the deployed site in a browser. For a local demonstration, a developer starts the Vite development server; then the user opens the displayed local address.')
heading('8.3 Using the Homepage and Navigation',2); p('Use the navigation bar or footer links to jump to a section. Choose a product-category link such as CEILING FANS to move to the catalogue with that category already selected. On a narrow screen, use the hamburger button to open the navigation panel. The Explore Collection button moves to products.')
heading('8.4 Browsing, Filtering and Sorting Products',2); p('At Products, use Category, Type, Price Range, Color and Brand controls. Colour circles toggle a colour selection. Choose a Sort By option to change the order. Use Clear Filters to return to all categories, all types/colours/brands, the maximum price and Popular sort. If nothing matches, the page says to adjust or clear filters.')
heading('8.5 Product Details, Favourites and Cart',2); p('Select View Details to open a product modal. Read the specifications and price, then choose Add to Cart or the heart button. Close using the X, by clicking outside the panel, or pressing Escape. The cart icon opens the cart drawer. Use minus/plus buttons to change quantities; reducing a line from one to zero removes it. Checkout is presently a visual button only and does not complete a purchase.')
heading('8.6 Gallery, Offers, FAQs and Contact',2); p('Select a gallery image to enlarge it; click the overlay to close. Offers show the items whose local data has an old price. Expand FAQ questions to read their answers. In Contact, enter a name, a syntactically valid email and a message; submit to receive a local confirmation. The message is not sent to an organisation in the current version.')
heading('8.7 Troubleshooting and Closing',2); table(['Issue','Action'],[['Product list appears empty','Use Clear Filters.'],['Modal will not close','Press Escape, click the close X, or click outside the panel.'],['Cart contents disappear','This is expected after a page refresh because cart state is not persisted.'],['Contact confirmation expected by email','The app does not transmit email; the confirmation is visual only.'],['Close the site','Close the browser tab. For local hosting, stop the Vite terminal with Ctrl+C.']], [2.2,4.8])

heading('9. Developer Guide',1)
heading('9.1 Installation and Commands',2); code('''npm install\nnpm run dev\nnpm run build\nnpm run preview\nnpm run lint'''); p('package.json defines these scripts. The project uses ESM ("type": "module"). Vite configuration registers only the React plugin. Bootstrap CSS and bundle JS are imported at startup so the FAQ collapse behaviour is available.')
heading('9.2 Component Hierarchy and Dependencies',2); p('App is the composition root. ProductSection depends on ProductFilter and ProductGrid; ProductGrid depends on ProductCard; ProductCard conditionally renders ProductModal. App also imports CartDrawer. Components import their paired CSS and Lucide icons where required. allProducts is read by ProductSection, Gallery and Offers.')
heading('9.3 Adding or Editing a Product',2); p('Edit src/data/products.js. Add an object with a unique numeric id, name, category, type, color, brand, comma-formatted price, rating, reviews, badge (if needed), imported image and description. oldPrice is optional; when present it causes Offers to include that record. Add a corresponding colour mapping in ProductSection.jsx if a new colour should show as an accurate filter swatch.')
heading('9.4 Extending Features',2); p('For persistence, replace local arrays with an API-backed data layer and move cart/favourites to authenticated server state or local storage. For functional contact, submit to a secure endpoint and surface asynchronous failure/success. For checkout, add a verified payment flow, server-side price calculation and order creation. Text search is not implemented and should be designed as a separate filter criterion rather than describing the present filter UI as search.')
heading('9.5 Styling, Debugging and Maintenance',2); p('Keep reusable styles within the component folder and reserve global.css for truly global rules. Preserve Bootstrap breakpoint classes where the layout depends on them. Verify modal cleanup, category-event listener cleanup and timer cleanup after changes. Use the Vite console and browser developer tools for runtime issues. Keep product price display and numeric conversion compatible, or migrate prices to numeric values at the API boundary.')
heading('9.6 Build and Deployment',2); p('The intended build command is npm run build, which invokes vite build and normally emits a deployable bundle to dist. During this report’s verification, the installed dependency set produced a Vite/Rolldown build error concerning an absolute/relative emitted index.html name. Resolve that environment/dependency issue and rerun the build before deploying; do not treat the existing dist directory as proof that the present build passes.')

heading('10. Module Descriptions',1)
table(['Module','Purpose, inputs/outputs and key relationships'],[['main.jsx','Imports Bootstrap/global CSS and mounts App in React StrictMode.'],['App.jsx','Top-level composition; owns favourites, cart and cart-drawer state; passes callbacks/counts.'],['Navbar','Anchor navigation, category CustomEvent dispatch, visitor counter, mobile overlay, favourite/cart indicators.'],['Ticker','Scrolling announcements and one-second display clock.'],['Hero','Hero asset, marketing content and scroll-to-products action.'],['Features','Four static feature cards.'],['ProductSection','Filter state, option derivation, CustomEvent listener, filtering/sorting and catalogue layout.'],['ProductFilter','Controlled filter controls; returns changes to ProductSection.'],['ProductGrid','Maps matching records to cards or shows no-results state.'],['ProductCard','Renders a product summary, favourite action and per-card modal state.'],['ProductModal','Displays detail; manages Escape/body-scroll lifecycle; triggers cart/favourite callbacks.'],['CartDrawer','Normalizes cart rows, calculates subtotal and exposes quantity/close actions.'],['Gallery','Derives first eight product images and controls a lightbox.'],['Offers','Selects oldPrice records and calculates percentage reductions.'],['About','Static company narrative and four statistics.'],['FAQ','Static FAQ data in Bootstrap accordion markup.'],['Contact','Controlled validation form and local confirmation state.'],['Footer','Static links, category filter dispatch and contact/social presentation.'],['products.js','15 local records; named allProducts and toNumber exports; default first-three subset.'],['CSS files','Component styling, motion and local responsive overrides.']], [1.55,5.45])

heading('11. Testing',1)
heading('11.1 Verification Performed',2); p('The source was inspected module-by-module and the configured build and lint commands were executed in the delivered workspace. No automated test suite is declared in package.json and no test files were found. Therefore, the functional/UI cases below are documented as manual test cases derived from code review and intended browser verification; they are not represented as an invented automated test run.')
table(['Test ID','Test case','Expected result','Actual / status'],[['T-01','Load page','All sections render in page order.','Code-reviewed; implementation present.'],['T-02','Choose a category navigation link','Products section scrolls and category filter updates.','Code-reviewed; CustomEvent/listener present.'],['T-03','Apply filters/sort','Only matching product cards display in requested order.','Code-reviewed; predicate/sort logic present.'],['T-04','Open/close details','Modal opens; X/backdrop/Escape close it and restore scroll.','Code-reviewed; lifecycle present.'],['T-05','Add/adjust cart item','Item is added/incremented; zero quantity removes it; subtotal updates.','Code-reviewed; state logic present.'],['T-06','Submit invalid contact form','Inline errors appear.','Code-reviewed; validate() present.'],['T-07','Submit valid contact form','Confirmation displays and fields clear; no message transmission.','Code-reviewed; local behaviour present.'],['T-08','Responsive UI','Grid/menu/modal changes at defined breakpoints.','Static CSS/Bootstrap review complete; browser matrix not executed.'],['T-09','npm run build','Production bundle should build.','Failed in inspected environment: Vite/Rolldown emitted-name error.'],['T-10','npm run lint','No lint errors expected.','Failed: react-hooks/set-state-in-effect in Navbar.jsx line 40.']], [.55,1.4,2.2,2.85])
heading('11.2 UI, Responsive, Cross-browser and Performance Testing',2); p('The project includes responsive rules but no committed device/browser test evidence or performance benchmark. Recommended completion testing is Chrome, Firefox, Edge and Safari at desktop, tablet and mobile widths; validate navigation, FAQ collapse, modal, lightbox, cart and contact states. Production performance should be measured only after the build failure has been resolved.')
heading('11.3 Bugs and Fixes / Observations',2); p('Observed build issue: vite build failed with a Rolldown error that an emitted index.html name was treated as an absolute/relative path. Observed lint issue: Navbar sets visitorCount synchronously in an effect, which the configured React Hooks lint rule rejects. These are report findings, not unverified claims that fixes have been applied. A functional limitation is that social anchors use # and do not target external social destinations.')

heading('12. Conclusion and Future Improvements',1)
heading('12.1 Objectives Achieved',2); p('The delivered project successfully demonstrates a coherent responsive React catalogue experience with 15 products, multi-criterion filtering, sorting, product-modal details, favourites, a temporary cart, gallery, offers, FAQ and contact validation. Its folder structure and local data model make the interface understandable and extendable.')
heading('12.2 Challenges and Lessons Learned',2); p('The project highlights the distinction between a convincing front-end interaction and a production transaction system. Local component state is effective for demonstration but is not durable. Storing formatted prices as strings also requires deliberate conversion before filtering and calculations. Cross-component interactions are managed by lifted state and a small custom browser event, avoiding a global state library.')
heading('12.3 Recommendations and Future Enhancements',2)
for x in ['Resolve the current build/lint findings and add automated component and end-to-end tests.','Add a backend API and normalized database based on the proposed schema.','Persist users, favourites, carts, contact messages and orders securely.','Implement authenticated checkout, payment integration, server-side price validation and order history.','Implement an actual product text search if required; it is not present now.','Add accessible keyboard/focus management for custom overlays, and conduct formal cross-browser/performance testing.','Replace placeholder company/contact information and capture final screenshots after deployment.']: bullet(x)
heading('12.4 Documentation Standards',2); p('This report distinguishes verified implementation from recommended production work. It does not claim backend services, persistence, payment, search or message delivery where the submitted source does not implement them. Before submission, the student should replace cover-page placeholders, update the automatic Table of Contents in Word, insert the numbered running-application screenshots and rerun build/lint after correcting the reported issues.')

